      • JEXData

        public JEXData(JEXData jd)
        Use this method to perform a deep copy of the jexdata object EXCEPT FOR LOAD NAME BECAUSE WE ARE CREATING NEW THINGS HERE THAT DON'T HAVE A LOAD LOCATION. WE ARE CREATING THEM. ALL DETACHED FILES ARE WRITTEN ANEW ANYWAYS. THE ONLY THING THAT WILL BE BAD IS FILE PATHS REFERENCED IN THE DETACHED FILE WILL NOT BE DUPLICATED. IN ORDER TO MAKE THIS A TRUE DEEP COPY WE WOULD HAVE TO COPY THE INFORMATION REFERENCED IN THE JEXDATASINGLE AS WELL. WHICH I DON'T THINK MAKES SENSE BECAUSE I DONT THINK WE WANT ANY TWO JEXDATA REFERENCING THE SAME FILES.
        Parameters:
        jd -
